Headline: Architect & Developer, ServiceNow MVP & CMA
Text: oops! forgot to demote myself to backstage! Just ignore the woman behind the curtain! üòÇ
Ty, are you default setting your app files to protected?  When do you ever set your files read-only or not?

Headline: Dev/Architect/Founder/Speaker
Text: We would normally protect all script includes to prevent enthusiastic devs from reverse engineering. Leave open for files which can/should be modified. Rarely if ever use read-only but could be useful if you wanted people to see exactly what your script is doing.

Headline: ServiceNow Developer
Bio: I am a ServiceNow Developer at K2 Services and one of the co-coordinators for WomenNow. I focus on UI development, custom components, and workspace design where I create engaging, intuitive experiences in ServiceNow. I love sharing creative UI Builder techniques through community events, talks, and labs that inspire others to build with confidence.
